issue.title: Reloader logs Kubernetes Secrets
issue.body:
Reloader sometimes logs `Secret` K8s resources. It could be a security issue in many production environments.

Real world example:

```
Update for '<deployment-name>' of type 'Deployment' in namespace '<namespace-name>' failed with error Operation cannot be fulfilled on deployments.apps "<deployment-name>": the object has been modified; please apply your changes to the latest version and try again

E1116 16:40:21.498716       1 controller.go:171] Operation cannot be fulfilled on deployments.apps "<deployment-name>": the object has been modified; please apply your changes to the latest version and try again

Dropping the key {"&Secret{ObjectMeta:{<entire-secret-resource-appeared-here>},Type:Opaque,StringData:map[string]string{},Immutable:*false,}" {%!q(*prometheus.CounterVec=&{0xc000219650})}} out of the queue: Operation cannot be fulfilled on deployments.apps "<deployment-name>": the object has been modified; please apply your changes to the latest version and try again
```

(I've masked the secret resource with `<entire-secret-resource-appeared-here>` above).

The "Dropping the key..." log event [is logged](https://github.com/stakater/Reloader/blob/50791ad51a0f1aa25d91ff7dfa0f1fbf861e7726/internal/pkg/controller/controller.go#L185) on `info` level which I don't think is appropriate. What about raising the level to error (the log event alone is a rare exception) but logging the entire resource only in debug?

```
logrus.Errorf("Dropping key out of the queue: %v", err)
logrus.Debugf("Dropping the key %q out of the queue: %v", key, err)
```

Also I can't find a way to raise the log level to workaround the issue until it's fixed.

Thanks!

comment.body: Fix has been released @moleskin-smile can you plz validate

issue.title: Reloader logs Kubernetes Secrets
issue.body:
Reloader sometimes logs `Secret` K8s resources. It could be a security issue in many production environments.

Real world example:

```
Update for '<deployment-name>' of type 'Deployment' in namespace '<namespace-name>' failed with error Operation cannot be fulfilled on deployments.apps "<deployment-name>": the object has been modified; please apply your changes to the latest version and try again

E1116 16:40:21.498716       1 controller.go:171] Operation cannot be fulfilled on deployments.apps "<deployment-name>": the object has been modified; please apply your changes to the latest version and try again

Dropping the key {"&Secret{ObjectMeta:{<entire-secret-resource-appeared-here>},Type:Opaque,StringData:map[string]string{},Immutable:*false,}" {%!q(*prometheus.CounterVec=&{0xc000219650})}} out of the queue: Operation cannot be fulfilled on deployments.apps "<deployment-name>": the object has been modified; please apply your changes to the latest version and try again
```

(I've masked the secret resource with `<entire-secret-resource-appeared-here>` above).

The "Dropping the key..." log event [is logged](https://github.com/stakater/Reloader/blob/50791ad51a0f1aa25d91ff7dfa0f1fbf861e7726/internal/pkg/controller/controller.go#L185) on `info` level which I don't think is appropriate. What about raising the level to error (the log event alone is a rare exception) but logging the entire resource only in debug?

```
logrus.Errorf("Dropping key out of the queue: %v", err)
logrus.Debugf("Dropping the key %q out of the queue: %v", key, err)
```

Also I can't find a way to raise the log level to workaround the issue until it's fixed.

Thanks!
